Package: psychdsish
Title: Create and Validate 'psych-DS'-Inspired Project Structures
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R:
    person("Ian", "Hussey", email = "ian.hussey@unibe.ch",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8906-7559"))
Description: Creates a standardised R project skeleton that is loosely
    inspired by the 'psych-DS' data standard (<https://psych-ds.github.io/>)
    for psychological data, and checks whether an existing project follows
    the same conventions. The layout is not fully 'psych-DS' compliant --
    most notably it drops the JSON metadata requirement -- hence
    'psych-DS-ish'. Alongside the directory structure it generates Quarto
    templates, a README, a licence, and a '.gitignore' with sensible
    defaults, and adds extra conventions for reproducibility and common
    'tidyverse' workflows. A validator function reports whether a project
    follows the conventions and, where it does not, how to fix it. See Hussey
    (2025) <doi:10.5281/zenodo.21441984> for the archived software record.
URL: https://github.com/ianhussey/psychdsish
